# Architecture Rules

Use Atomic Design for UI organization.

Definitions:

Atoms:

- Small reusable UI elements
- Must not contain business logic

Examples:

- Button
- Input
- Icon
- Badge

Molecules:

- Combination of atoms
- Small reusable compositions

Examples:

- SearchInput
- FormField
- UserCard

Organisms:

- Larger composed sections
- May integrate hooks and interactions

Examples:

- Sidebar
- Header
- LoginForm

Templates:

- Layout structures only
- No business rules

Pages:

- Final composition
- Connect data and UI

Rules:

- Business logic never belongs inside components
- Components focus on rendering
- Complex logic belongs in hooks
- External communication belongs in services
- Avoid circular dependencies

